/*

https://datalemur.com/questions/teams-power-users

Sargable means Search ARGument able â€” a condition in your WHERE, JOIN, or ON clause that the database can use to search via an index efficiently.

In simple words:

A sargable filter allows the database to use an index seek or range scan instead of scanning every row.

If index is not there on the column scans full table, but still effiective because of the simple comparsion

*/

SELECT sender_id, count(*) 
FROM messages
where sent_date >= '2022-08-01' and sent_date < '2022-09-01' --Sargable (Search ARgumentABLE)
group by 1
order by 2 desc
limit 2;
